name: ABC
summary: Biden has stated in an exclusive interview that US weapons will not be used to target Moscow or the Kremlin. Additionally, he indicated he would not pardon his son Hunter and believes Trump received a fair trial. Other news headlines include: Video footage from Israel shows significant progress in Gaza; John Kirby anticipates Israel's acceptance of a proposed deal if Hamas does; and half of Americans believe Trump's guilty verdict is valid and should end his campaign. Furthermore, the Trump team has requested documents from potential vice presidential candidates Burgum, Vance, and Rubio. Donald Trump has responded to Nikki Haley's declaration of support, indicating that she may eventually join their team. Finally, ABC's David Muir will interview Biden in France regarding the 2024 US elections.

name: BJ Thompson
summary: Kansas City Chiefs lineman BJ Thompson suffered a cardiac arrest during a team meeting. He required a defibrillator shock to restart his heart. Reports indicate that Thompson is now stable but remains unconscious. Chiefs' defensive coordinator Steve Spagnuolo has commented on the incident, expressing concern for Thompson's well-being. Thompson's agent has stated that he is awake and responsive, one day after the event. Teammates, including Harrison Butker, played a crucial role in alerting trainers and assisting Thompson during his seizure and cardiac arrest. Thompson's current condition is stable, and he is receiving medical attention at a hospital.
